misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that in order to shift an array of size N one position to the right (with wrapping), they must first save the element at index N-1, then use a loop running backwards from N-1 down to 1 to overwrite x[i] with x[i-1], and finally assign the saved element to x[0].
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: There is no conceptual gap. The code correctly implements the necessary steps for an array right shift (rotation) in a single pass using temporary storage, demonstrating a sound understanding of array indexing and sequential assignment.
